Sentencas: Sm1-xCexFeO3-delta (x = 0-0.05) perovskite materials were investigated as anodes for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs) using dry hydrogen and dry methane fuels.
Titulo: Chemically stable and coke resistant Sm1-xCexFeO3-δ perovskites for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell anode applications

Sentencas: Ce doping changes the electrical behaviour of SmFeO3 from p-type to n-type and improves the reduction stability under the strong reducing atmosphere required at the anode.
Titulo: Chemically stable and coke resistant Sm1-xCexFeO3-δ perovskites for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell anode applications

Sentencas: The resulting Ce doped materials presented good and stable performances as anodes under hydrogen and methane fuels.
Titulo: Chemically stable and coke resistant Sm1-xCexFeO3-δ perovskites for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell anode applications

Sentencas: The Sm0.95Ce0.05FeO3-delta anode showed the lowest charge transfer resistances in the series at 700 degrees C, 0.05 Omega cm(2) and 1.4 Omega cm(2) under dry hydrogen and methane, respectively.
Titulo: Chemically stable and coke resistant Sm1-xCexFeO3-δ perovskites for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell anode applications

Sentencas: At 450 degrees C, the Sm0.95Ce0.01FeO3-delta anode demonstrated performance with an open circuit potential (OCP) of 0.690 V and lowest R-ct of 1.5 k Omega cm(2) under dry methane fuel.
Titulo: Chemically stable and coke resistant Sm1-xCexFeO3-δ perovskites for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell anode applications

Sentencas: More importantly no visible coking was found on the surface of these anodes after the performance under dry methane for similar to 23 h at all temperatures.
Titulo: Chemically stable and coke resistant Sm1-xCexFeO3-δ perovskites for low temperature solid oxide fuel cell anode applications
